messages.content: ComfyUI-ResAdapter is an extension that enhances the usability of ResAdapter by providing a simple node to load resadapter weights and offering specific workflows for text-to-image, accelerate-lora, controlnet and ip-adapter.
To install ComfyUI-ResAdapter, you need to clone the ComfyUI-ResAdapter repository, move it to ComfyUI/custom_nodes/ and select 'Load ResAdapter Node' in ComfyUI.
How can you download models for ComfyUI-ResAdapter?

ComfyUI-ResAdapter provides a script for automatically downloading resadapter models from Hugging Face in the __init__.py file. Alternatively, you can directly download models from the Hugging Face website.
Where can you find example workflows for ComfyUI-ResAdapter?
Example workflows for ComfyUI-ResAdapter can be found in the 'examples' directory of the repository.
What models are used in the ControlNet example workflow?
The ControlNet example workflow uses stable-diffusion-v1-5 and sd-controlnet-canny models.
What models are used in the IPAdapter example workflow?
The IPAdapter example workflow uses stable-diffusion-v1-5 and IP-Adapter models.
What models are used in the Accelerate LoRA example workflow?
The Accelerate LoRA example workflow uses stable-diffusion-v1-5 and lcm-lora-sdv1-5 models.
